2. facet_grid(sex~race)

p = ggplot(data = gss_sm, mapping = aes(x = age, y = childs))
p + geom_point(alpha = 0.2) +
    geom_smooth() + 
    facet_grid(sex ~ race)

p = ggplot(data = gss_sm, mapping = aes(x = age, y = childs))
p + geom_point(alpha = 0.2) +
    geom_smooth() + 
    facet_grid(~ sex + race)

The difference is that in the second facet grid we kind of making a filter based on sex + race as it was mentioned in this chapter because we have contiguous table.

3. facet_wrap(~ sex + race)

p = ggplot(data = gss_sm, mapping = aes(x = age, y = childs))
p + geom_point(alpha = 0.2) +
    geom_smooth() + 
    facet_wrap(~ sex + race)

There is an interesting difference betwee facet_grid and facet_wrap
